**Javascript Functions**
JavaScripts function is executed when your Program is calling it (invokes it)
n```js
function myFirstFunction(a1, a2) {
  return a1 + a2;

}```
*The function returns the product of a1 and a2*!

**Javascript Functions - Return**
When there is an `return` statement, the Program will stop executing there.
n```js
let z = mySecondFunction(2, 2)

function mySecondFunction(a, b) {

  return a * b; // Function returns the Product of a and b

}```
When there is an `return` statement, the Program will stop executing there.
The result here is `4`
